This file can be run with Z3Py as:

> teaparty.py <input_file> <output_file>

where the format of the contents of <input_file> must be:

<switch distance S>
<sequence of occupied seats (i n), indicating guest i is at seat n>
<guests that must change places>

For example, a valid input file may look like:

4
(0 0) (1 4) (2 5) (3 7)
1 2 3
